g.ns0:text: here, there is a derivative of every equivalent codevector w.r.t. $\mathbf{z}_{\rho,k}$
but we should consider only those equivalent codevectors $\mathbf{y}_j$ that contain $\mathbf{z}_{\rho,k}$ in their sum, i.e. $j \in H_{\rho, k}$

$			
\begin{array}{lllll}
e 
&= \sum\limits_{k=1}^{K}\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_k}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_k}}(x_i-\hat{m}_k)^2 	\\ \\

&=
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_1}}(x_i-\hat{m}_1)^2p_X(x_i) 	+	\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_2}}(x_i-\hat{m}_2)^2p_X(x_i) +	\ldots 	+	\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_K}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_K}}(x_i-\hat{m}_K)^2p_X(x_i)	\\ \\ \\ \\

\frac{\partial e}{\partial z_{a, b}} 	
&=\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{i,1}}2(x_i-\hat{m}_1)\frac{\partial \hat{m}_1}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}}p_X(x_i)	+ \sum\limits_{i=1 \atop \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{i,2}}2(x_i-m_2)\frac{\partial m_2}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}}p_X(x_i) 	+ \ldots 	+ \sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in K_{N_k}}^{N_{i,N_k}}2(x_i-\hat{m}_{N_k})\frac{\partial \hat{m}_{N_k}}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}}p_X(x_i)		\\ \\ \\

&= 
\sum\limits_{j \in H_{\alpha, \beta}}\int\limits_{S_j}2(x-\hat{m}_k)\frac{\partial y_j}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}}f_X(x)dx					\\ \\

&=
\sum\limits_{j \in H_{\rho,k}}\int\limits_{S_j}2\left(x-\left[\sum\limits_{\alpha=0,\alpha \neq \alpha}^{P-1}y_{j,p} + z_{\alpha, \beta}\right]\right)\frac{\partial \left[\sum\limits_{p=0,p \neq \rho}^{P-1}y_{j,p} + z_{\alpha, \beta}\right]}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}}f_X(x)dx 	\\ \\
&=\sum\limits_{j \in H_{\alpha, \beta}}\int\limits_{S_j}2\left(x-\left[\sum\limits_{p=0,p \neq \alpha}^{P-1}y_{j,p} + z_{\alpha, \beta}\right]\right)f_X(x)dx 	\\ \\
\mbox{let } \frac{\partial e}{\partial z_{\alpha, \beta}} 				&=0		\\
\Rightarrow z_{\rho,k}	&=	\frac{\sum\limits_{j \in H_{\alpha, \beta}}\int\limits_{S_j}\left(x-\sum\limits_{p=0,p \neq \alpha}^{P-1}y_{j,p}\right)f_X(x)dx}{\sum\limits_{j \in H_{\alpha, \beta}}\int\limits_{S_j}f_X(x)dx}
\end{array}
$

$\begin{array}{ll}
A			&: \mbox{number of stages}\\
B			&: \mbox{number of templates per stage}\\
K			&: \mbox{number of clusters= number of equivalent code-vectors}\\
& \mbox{=number of paths through trellis=number of SoC descriptors}=B^A\\ \\


a			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, A\}\\
b			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, B\}\\
k			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, K\}\\ \\


e			&: \mbox{mean squared error between inputs and reconstructed inputs}\\
\mathcal{K}_k			&: \mbox{$k$-th cluster}\\
\hat{m}_k		&: \mbox{$k$-th mean, i.e. $k$-th equivalent code-vector (uses $k$-th SoC descriptor)}\\
\hat{m}_{k,a}		&: \mbox{$a$-th additive stage-codevector component of $\hat{m}_k$}\\
N_{\mathcal{K}_k} 			&: \mbox{number of input data points that map to the $k$-th cluster}\\ \\



H_{a, b}	&: \mbox{set of indeces of trellis paths that go through $z_{a,b}$ stage code-vector}\\
z_{a,b}	&: \mbox{stage code-vector, $b$-th template at $a$-th stage}\\
\end{array}
$
